reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 25, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Very useful, great for narrow spaces
reviews.reviewText: Excellent little cabinet perfect for extra paper roll, spray and other little items. Assembly super easy. Don't panic when you see all the prices, the directions are excellent.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 28, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great purchase - fits need and looks nice
reviews.reviewText: This was very easy to assemble - my 5 year old daughter was able to help. It is made out of some type of composite material and seems to be very sturdy. I was concerned that the toilet paper holder bar felt light and was worried it might not hold up, but it spins freely without any issues so far. The cabinet underneath is wide enough to hold the Charmin mega rolls of toilet paper. The small shelf on top is the perfect size to hold a pack of wet wipes and a spray bottle of poo-pourri.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Fits in my small space.
reviews.reviewText: I wanted a small cabinet to put in a small bathroom to keep extra toilet tissue and a few other things. This cabinet fits perfect and was quite easy to assemble.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 24, 2021
reviews.reviewText: It was easy to put together. You’ll need a screw driver to properly do it. The height reflected what the Amazon “see in your room” feature guesstimated. The color is good. The toilet roll works great. If I had to buy it again, I’d certainly do so. And before I figured out how to dispense the toilet paper from the talker version of this one, I considered returning that one abs getting this one again instead.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 25, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Cheap but low risk
reviews.reviewText: It looks cheap and feels cheap but if you just need something to “get you by” then it’s really not a bad investment - or if it’s usually concealed somewhere then it’s also not a bad buy. I don’t actually use mine for toilet paper (I put products in the bottom instead and stacked makeup in the upper compartment) but given the structure of it, I can’t imagine it’s too sturdy trying to pull toilet paper out of.

reviews.reviewText: This is way better than the other one looks good

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 28, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Looks can be deceiving
reviews.reviewText: I dislike how thei is really no space for storage. It's very disappointing. Easy to install.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 11, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 2.0 out of 5 stars Not as sturdy as I thought.
reviews.reviewText: First off ignore the photo bomber, although you can see the difference in size :)Use a regular screw driver to put in screws and no hammer or it will crumble, it's kind of easy to put together it's mostly interlocking pieces like a puzzle. I found several thing's I would do differently when putting it together. The broken piece happened when I was trying to push the panel in the interlocking spot with my palm. When attaching the toilet paper to the holder and trying to place it, its really hard since there is not much room. I use Charmin so I guess it would be easier with say, Scott's. The material is Gypsum with a thin laminate almost like paper on top. You will need to attach the knob before you attach the front panel. It will save you frustration.

reviews.reviewTitle: Small but works for small spaces
reviews.reviewText: Works for small spaces. We didn’t use the toilet paper area. I put product that would fit there.
